@startuml brake_lamp_and_abs_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Brake Lamp And ABS Signal Flow\n(Input_Console -> ESC -> ABS -> CLU)

actor "Driver\n(Input Console)" as Driver #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nVehicle > Pedal + Cruise" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "VCU\nvehicle speed owner" as VCU #E8F7E8
participant "ESC\nbrake / brake-lamp owner" as ESC #FFE6E6
participant "ABS\nwheel-slip / pressure command" as ABS #FFF4CC
participant "CLU\nvehicle readback" as CLU #E8F0FE

== Brake Command ==

Driver -> Panel : Press brake pedal
activate Panel
Panel -> Panel : Write Cmd::brakePedalPct
deactivate Panel

== Vehicle State For Brake Logic ==

activate VCU
Panel -> VCU : Optional speed / drive-state aid
VCU -> ESC : frmVehicleStateCanMsg
VCU -> ESC : frmWheelPulseMsg
note right of VCU
Vehicle state provides
- speedNorm basis
- driveState basis
- wheel pulse cadence
end note
deactivate VCU

== ESC Brake Ownership ==

activate ESC
Panel -> ESC : Cmd::brakePedalPct
VCU -> ESC : frmVehicleStateCanMsg
ESC -> ESC : appliedBrakePedal = Cmd::brakePedalPct
ESC -> ESC : absActive = (pedal > 80 && speedNorm > 10)
ESC -> ESC : Chassis::brakeLamp = (pedal > 5)
ESC -> ESC : Chassis::absActive = absActive
ESC -> ABS : frmBrakeStatusMsg\nBrakePressure / BrakeMode / AbsActive
ESC -> ABS : frmWheelSpeedMsg
ESC -> CLU : Chassis::brakePressure / brakeLamp / absActive
note right of ESC
Representative outputs
- frmBrakeStatusMsg
- frmWheelSpeedMsg
- Chassis::brakeLamp
- Chassis::absActive
end note
deactivate ESC

== ABS Response ==

activate ABS
ESC -> ABS : frmBrakeStatusMsg
ESC -> ABS : frmWheelSpeedMsg
ABS -> ABS : pressureCmd = brakePressure when absActive
ABS -> ABS : AbsCtrlState = 2 when active
ABS -> ABS : output frmAbsStateMsg
note right of ABS
Representative logic
- brake input stale handling
- wheel-speed stale handling
- rear wheel average and slip reaction
end note
deactivate ABS

== Driver Visible Outcome ==

activate CLU
ESC -> CLU : Chassis::brakeLamp / absActive
CLU -> Panel : brake/ABS readback
deactivate CLU

Driver <- Panel : Brake lamp and ABS state follow the brake event

note over Driver, CLU
Representative runtime chain
1. Driver presses brake
2. ESC owns brake pressure and brake lamp state
3. ESC publishes brake + wheel-speed status to ABS
4. ABS derives pressure command / control state
5. CLU and panel show brake-lamp / ABS feedback
end note

@enduml
